# Revisions for `git blame` to skip: bulk reformats and renames that touch
# many lines without changing behaviour, and would otherwise bury the commit
# that actually wrote each line.
#
# GitHub applies this automatically. Locally it needs to be switched on once
# per clone (it cannot be tracked, being repo config rather than content):
#
#   git config blame.ignoreRevsFile .git-blame-ignore-revs
#
# Entries must be full 40-character SHAs — git rejects abbreviated ones — and
# each one should say what it was, since a bare hash tells the next reader
# nothing.

